'''Enrique O. Aragón''' (1880–1942) was a [[Mexico|Mexican]] philosopher and physician, once alternative rector of Mexico's National Autonomous University.

He studied in the National Preparatory school and on 1891 got into the National School of Medicin, where he reached his degree as a doctor, surgeon, and obstetrician on 12th April 1904.

He died on 1942. There is a highschool with his name in Iztapalapa, Federal District.

