'''Lake Rangrim''', also known as '''Lake Nangnim''', is an artificial lake in the [[Rangrim Mountains]] of [[Chagang Province]] in northern [[North Korea]]. It was formed by [[dam]]ming a river valley to produce [[hydroelectricity]]. The lake, with its adjacent [[temperate broadleaf and mixed forest]] habitats, has been identified by [[BirdLife International]] as an 8600&nbsp;ha [[Important Bird Area]] (IBA). The IBA lies at an altitude of 700–1700&nbsp;m above sea level.<ref name=bli>{{cite web |url= http://www.birdlife.org |title= Lake Rangrim |accessdate=2013-05-06 |work= Important Bird Areas factsheet |first= |last= |publisher= BirdLife International |year= 2013}}</ref>

